Press any key to begin
Mandatory rest break before the start of the next run
The experiment is now complete. Thank you for your participation!
Please call your experimenter.
In this experiment, we are going to measure your thresholds for detecting a visual pattern that looks like this:
On each trial, we will briefly flash the pattern in one of the four positions below. You will then be asked to indicate which position you thought the pattern was presented in.
You indicate your choice by pressing numbers on the keypad as shown below:
To vary the difficulty of this task, the pattern will be shown at different contrasts. Below shows the pattern at different contrasts, from low (left, hard) to high (right, easy):
The difficulty will be automatically adjusted based on your previous responses, so you will always be getting some trials correct and some trials incorrect.
After your response, a marker will appear in the location of the pattern. If you chose correctly, the marker will be a 'tick'. If you chose incorrectly, the marker will be a 'cross'.
At all times during each trial, please keep your gaze focused on the small circle in the centre.
We will now do a few example trials.
Remember to:
* Keep your gaze on the central circle
* Try and detect at which location the pattern was presented
* Respond using the numbers on the keypad
We will now do a practice run with trials like what you have just been doing.
Please call your experimenter to proceed.
In the experiment, the target locations will be surrounded by a pattern that looks either like this:
Or like this:
Your task remains the same - to indicate which of the four spatial locations contained the target.
We will now do a few example trials where the surrounding pattern will be present.
You are now ready to begin the experiment.
Please call the experimenter, who can also answer any questions you might have at this stage.
